description.narrative: More than 85,370 children and their families in communities were reached with awareness campaigns to practice healthy behaviors on safe handling and storage of water, while 308 schools reached with awareness raising and trainings on hand-washing with soap particularly in most vulnerable districts in Central, Southern and KRI governorates through different modalities, including key messages disseminated through social media. Wide media coverage via Iraqi satellite channels, weekly TV interviews and debates with participation of decision makers and academia to discuss the importance of water quality, water contamination, impact of climate change, advocacy on healthier environment, water conservation and hygiene promotion | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/01/2019
